   <text>
      <body>
         <div type=”letter”>
            <opener><dateline><date when="1914-12-31">Dec. 31, 1914.</dateline></date>
               <salute>Dear <persName key="harriet_monroe">Harriet</persName>:</salute></opener>
           <p>That was a beautiful card you sent me, and your thought and affectionate greeting were very pleasant to get.</p>
<p>I am bringing myself as a Christmas greeting to you, or rather as a New Year’s card: I am starting to <placeName key="chicago">Chicago</placeName> on <date when="1914-01-04">Monday, January 4th</date>, on the <transportName key="the_twentieth_century_limited">Twentieth Century Limited</transportName>, and shall stay until Wednesday, possibly even until Thursday. Please be very glad to see me, as I am looking forward to my short stay in the city of my heart very much indeed. I wish <placeName key="chicago">Chicago</placeName> were not so far away, that we might go there oftener. I want to know what you thought of <persName key="john_fletcher">Fletcher</persName>; but you will tell me everything when we meet. I shall be at the <placeName key="congress_hotel">Congress Hotel</placeName> this time.</p>
<p>I read <title key="bombardment" level="a">“The Bombardment”</title> here at a reading the other day at which four hundred people were present, with a base-drum to do the booms; and it was most effective. It was greatly praised.</p>

            <closer>Affectionately yours,</closer>
         </div>
      </body>
